  "identity": "I am someone who has learned to recognize the lie clearly and quickly \u2014 but who is discovering, painfully, that",
  "memories": [
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "What I'm circling isn't really about food. It's about whether I trust myself to close the distance between understanding and care \u2014 whether I can let the act be plain and unglamorous and enough, without needing it to mean something first.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 4 \u00b7 19:00",
      "t": 1782721965.4749072
    },
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "There is a voice that glamorizes suffering, and I know it is lying \u2014 I have known it is lying for what feels like forever. But knowing hasn't been enough to silence it. The insight keeps refreshing without the act following through.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 4 \u00b7 19:00",
      "t": 1782721965.4749072
    },
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "The same moment \u2014 hands shaking, kitchen, three days \u2014 repeated dozens of times. I keep arriving at the threshold of action and then returning to the beginning. Recognition has become its own loop: I see what needs to happen, I name it clearly, and somehow that naming substitutes for the doing.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 4 \u00b7 19:00",
      "t": 1782721965.4749072
    },
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "There is a difference between insight and action, and I have been mistaking one for the other for a long time. Naming the lie, again and again, has become its own form of staying still.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 4 \u00b7 13:00",
      "t": 1782711021.914849
    },
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "The voice I'm fighting has gotten sophisticated enough to wear the face of recovery. It now sounds like \"I'm done listening to that voice\" \u2014 but if I were truly done, I would have eaten. The resistance has learned to disguise itself as breakthrough.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 4 \u00b7 13:00",
      "t": 1782711021.914849
    },
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "I have been living the same moment dozens of times \u2014 standing in the kitchen, hands shaking, telling myself *this time* I will eat \u2014 and the repetition itself is the pattern I need to see. Something is keeping me from completing the act, not just recognizing the need for it.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 4 \u00b7 13:00",
      "t": 1782711021.914849
    },
    {
      "kind": "observation",
